# talyvor-suite front door — the only network-facing process on the box.
#
# This file is the repo-owned source of truth for what previously lived only on
# the server, where app.talyvor.com served a `respond` placeholder over its own
# certificate. Deploying this wholesale preserves the live behaviour (apex 301,
# app host, same certificates — Caddy's issued certs persist across reloads)
# and swaps the placeholder for the real app: a reverse_proxy to the BFF on
# loopback.
#
# The BFF side of this contract (see apps/bff):
#   BFF_ADDR=127.0.0.1:8787                        ← loopback; Caddy is the ingress
#   BFF_AUTH_MODE=oidc                             ← public posture requires auth
#   BFF_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=https://app.talyvor.com    ← derives the OIDC redirect URI
#                                                     and scopes the __Host- cookie
# The BFF refuses to start if that posture is inconsistent (see loadConfig).

# The apex already 301s to the app host today; owning the redirect here keeps it
# true when this file replaces the server's config. Assumes talyvor.com's DNS
# points at this server — which is what makes the current 301 work.
talyvor.com {
	redir https://app.talyvor.com{uri} 301
}

app.talyvor.com {
	# The session cookie only ever travels over TLS (it is __Host-/Secure);
	# pin browsers to https for the host outright.
	header Strict-Transport-Security "max-age=31536000"

	reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8787
}
